{"key":"post-8904351","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8904351</id>\n<content>Mushroom size is related to substrate size and moisture content.&amp;nbsp; You MUST mist during the flush to replace the moisture that evaporates.&amp;nbsp; Since the size of the substrate is fixed with cakes, the size of the fruits depends on moisture content.&amp;nbsp; Dunk your cakes before first flush and between flushes.&amp;nbsp; Mist as required to keep the cake moist and the air at near 100% humidity, while providing lots of fresh air.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8906025</next>\n<prev>8904341</prev>\n<first>8904007</first>\n<last>8906060</last>\n<when>1221016094</when>\n<utime>09/10/08 06:08 AM</utime>\n</post>"}